  "prompt": "Does carnotaurus have slitted eyes pupils too or doesn't?",
  "response": "There isn't definitive evidence to confirm whether Carnotaurus, a theropod dinosaur that lived approximately 70 million years ago during the Late Cretaceous period, had slitted or round pupils. Fossilized remains generally do not preserve soft tissues such as eyes, so paleontologists have to infer eye characteristics from related species and available evidence. Inferences about the visual anatomy of dinosaurs like Carnotaurus are based on comparisons with modern reptiles and birds, which have a variety of pupil shapes. Until more direct evidence is found, the exact nature of Carnotaurus\u2019s eyes remains speculative.",
